<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1474,2005]" box="[199,1007,1509,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
Length and width: 13.43–15.73× 
<quantity box="[564,730,1509,1537]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.16" metricValueMax="4.23" metricValueMin="4.09" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="4.16" valueMax="4.23" valueMin="4.09">4.09–4.23 mm</quantity>
(average 14.6× 
<quantity box="[903,995,1510,1537]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1474,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
Plate of head projection blade smoothly rounded and shorter than half of its width in dorsal view. Frontal setae situated slightly behind the level of lateral angles of frons in dorsal view. Depressions on frons small, shallow and with radiant wrinkles (
<figureCitation box="[408,491,1618,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,260,1917,1944]" captionTargetBox="[319,1305,244,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[242,1345,216,1849]" captionText="FIGURE 6. Morphology of Bembecia lomatiaeformis pupa: a. Dorsal view of frons, b. Lateral view of frons, c. Labrum and vicinity, d. Abdominal end ventrally (male). Scale bar: a, c—0.5 mm; b, d—0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3448448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3448448/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
). Dark margin of head projection narrow and no curved in lateral view. Frons rises from blade of projection steeply in lateral view. Lateral depression on head relatively narrow and concave caudoventrally (
<figureCitation box="[266,349,1690,1717]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,260,1917,1944]" captionTargetBox="[319,1305,244,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[242,1345,216,1849]" captionText="FIGURE 6. Morphology of Bembecia lomatiaeformis pupa: a. Dorsal view of frons, b. Lateral view of frons, c. Labrum and vicinity, d. Abdominal end ventrally (male). Scale bar: a, c—0.5 mm; b, d—0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3448448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3448448/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Fig. 6b</figureCitation>
). Clypeal setae Cl 
<subScript attach="left" box="[553,561,1708,1722]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">2</subScript>
close to each other. Distance between setae Cl 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1083,1091,1708,1722]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">2</subScript>
approximately 2× greater than the distance of C1 
<subScript attach="left" box="[357,365,1744,1758]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">2</subScript>
from Cl 
<subScript attach="left" box="[463,475,1744,1758]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">1.</subScript>
Postclypeus separated from labrum by a dark rim. Labrum relatively long and large, rounded at end, with a small depression (
<figureCitation box="[633,718,1762,1789]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,260,1917,1944]" captionTargetBox="[319,1305,244,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[242,1345,216,1849]" captionText="FIGURE 6. Morphology of Bembecia lomatiaeformis pupa: a. Dorsal view of frons, b. Lateral view of frons, c. Labrum and vicinity, d. Abdominal end ventrally (male). Scale bar: a, c—0.5 mm; b, d—0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3448448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3448448/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
). End of abdomen in ventral view heart-shaped and distinctly pointed at end. Cremaster approximately equal in length to anal suture in male. In female distinctly shorter than anal suture. Anal area slightly convex (
<figureCitation box="[534,618,1834,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,260,1917,1944]" captionTargetBox="[319,1305,244,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[242,1345,216,1849]" captionText="FIGURE 6. Morphology of Bembecia lomatiaeformis pupa: a. Dorsal view of frons, b. Lateral view of frons, c. Labrum and vicinity, d. Abdominal end ventrally (male). Scale bar: a, c—0.5 mm; b, d—0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3448448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3448448/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Fig. 6d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1474,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1869,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lederer" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[328,529,1870,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lomatiaeformis">
<emphasis box="[328,345,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[359,529,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">lomatiaeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from other study species by the presence of short, and not curved in lateral view head projection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1191,1941,1969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1474,2005]" box="[199,1191,1941,1969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
